  "lastCommit": {
    "hash": "52b8572",
    "message": "fix: Settings panel drill-down UI — eliminates iPad scroll issue\n\nRestructured Settings from a single long scrollable page to a drill-down\npattern: main screen shows a compact list of 12 section cards (fits one\nscreen, no scrolling needed), tapping a card opens that section full-screen\nwith a back button. Completely sidesteps the iOS Safari fixed-container\nscroll bug. Inner section detail views use h-dvh flex layout matching\nPosModal's working pattern.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
    "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
    "date": "2026-03-13"
  },
  "recentCommits": [
    {
      "hash": "52b8572",
      "message": "fix: Settings panel drill-down UI — eliminates iPad scroll issue\n\nRestructured Settings from a single long scrollable page to a drill-down\npattern: main screen shows a compact list of 12 section cards (fits one\nscreen, no scrolling needed), tapping a card opens that section full-screen\nwith a back button. Completely sidesteps the iOS Safari fixed-container\nscroll bug. Inner section detail views use h-dvh flex layout matching\nPosModal's working pattern.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "5a5d43d",
      "message": "fix: course mapping breaks item rendering + Settings scroll on iPad\n\n- API was storing parseInt(\"main\",10) → NaN → 1 for ALL courses.\n  Added COURSE_TO_NUM lookup so drink=1, appetizer=2, soup=3, main=4, dessert=5.\n- dbItemToPosItem was converting course_number back as String(1)=\"1\" which\n  didn't match OrderPanel's COURSE_ORDER. Added COURSE_NUM_TO_NAME reverse map.\n- Settings panel: added h-dvh overflow-hidden to fixed motion.div for iOS Safari\n  flex height computation (matches PosModal's working pattern).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "643d931",
      "message": "fix: remove server_name from transactions INSERT — column does not exist\n\nThe server_name column was added in 452b0db but the DB schema was never\nmigrated, causing a 500 on every order creation attempt.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "296c0be",
      "message": "fix: iPad scroll + Add to Order error handling + order creation reliability\n\n1. PwaShell: change overflow-hidden to overflow-y-auto on content wrapper\n   so pages can scroll on iPad (overflow-hidden was clipping content)\n\n2. PwaSettingsPanel: add overscroll-y-contain to scroll container for\n   better iOS scroll behavior inside the fixed-position portal\n\n3. PosModal handleDetailAdd: wrap addItemToOrder in try/catch with\n   finally → setSelectedMenuItem(null). Previously, if addItemToOrder\n   threw (API error), the error was an unhandled rejection and the\n   detail sheet never closed — \"nothing happens\" on tap.\n\n4. PosModal handleItemTap quick-add: same try/catch treatment\n\n5. pos-store createPosOrder: remove silent fallback that returned a fake\n   order with a UUID not backed by DB. Now propagates errors so the\n   caller knows creation failed. Previously, all subsequent addItem\n   calls would fail because the order didn't exist in the database.\n\n6. PosModal init effect: show \"Could not start order\" error with Close\n   button when createPosOrder fails, instead of infinite spinner.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "f5d1358",
      "message": "fix: await DB order creation before showing menu — eliminates iPad add-to-order race\n\nThe \"Add to Order\" button was silently failing on iPad because the menu\nwas shown immediately with a local-only order ID while createPosOrder\nran in the background. Handlers polled dbOrderId ref for up to 5s and\nsilently returned if it never resolved.\n\nNow the \"Starting order...\" spinner stays visible until createPosOrder\nreturns a real DB order ID. The menu is only accessible after that, so\norder.id is always valid. Removes dbOrderId ref, polling loops, local\norder seeding, and migration logic.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "6cf72e0",
      "message": "fix: Settings panel white-screen crash — property mismatch + ErrorBoundary\n\nRoot cause: CategoryPrinterRouting declared MenuCategory with 'title' but\n/api/pwa/menu returns categories with 'name'. cat.title was undefined, so\n.toLowerCase() threw a TypeError during render. No ErrorBoundary existed,\nso React 19 unmounted the entire root → white screen after ~1s.\n\nFixes:\n1. CategoryPrinterRouting: align MenuCategory interface to API shape\n   (id: string, name: string), fix all cat.title → cat.name refs\n2. CategoryPrinterRouting: normalize printer DB shape (ip_address →\n   ip, printer_type → isKitchenPrinter, is_active → isActive)\n3. PwaSettingsPanel: wrap all settings content in SettingsErrorBoundary\n   — future render crashes show error message + Close button instead\n   of white-screening the PWA\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
      "date": "2026-03-13"
    },
    {
      "hash": "452b0db",
      "message": "fix: active orders missing held/check-dropped statuses, server_name not saved\n\nTwo bugs causing \"No active orders\" in PhoneOrdersTab:\n\n1. /api/pwa/orders/active SQL only queried for status IN ('open','fired',\n   'partial_pay') — missing 'held' and 'check-dropped'. Orders in those\n   states disappeared from the list.\n\n2. POST /api/pwa/orders never wrote server_name to the DB despite receiving\n   it in the request body. The \"Your Tables\" split (server_name === user.name)\n   always returned empty.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
      "branch": "feature/beta-onboarding",
